history.content:
I personally think the swap is not enabled in your scenario and you're good.

Also, you can confirm this by checking your email. If you have a class on swap, the system sends you an email every week entailing the details of your swap, starting from the day you swapped the class..

What about after you had enrolled in 61B, did you still get the emails?

In the email, it is clearly stated that dropping one of the concerned classes cancels the swap so this should not happen.

Ahh, thank you!

I was still getting the emails even when I had dropped the class and hadn't yet re-enrolled for 61b however. Does that mean that the swap is still in effect?

history.content:
I initially swapped in 126 for 61B during phase I because 126 was shown as open to me, and I thought I would just add 61B in phase II. However, upon enrollment, I was put at #26 on the waitlist spot. I was concerned that I would not be cleared from the 126 waitlist for a while, at which point it would be too late to enroll in 61B, so I decided to drop the class as well, and have since re-enrolled in it in phase II.

I am not sure, however, if the swap will still take effect despite me dropping the class and re-adding it. Does anyone know if it will? If it will still drop me from 61B upon enrollment in 126, then is there any one I can contact to help prevent that from taking place?

Thank you!
